0
00:00:49,929 --> 00:00:50,929
Belva!

1
00:00:51,850 --> 00:00:53,833
Are you checking on Faye?

2
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:57,713
She didn't walk me to the store yesterday.

3
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:02,569
I know Mrs. Hamill, you've
already told me twice!

4
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:06,619
And the smell coming out
of her room can gag a maggot!

5
00:01:06,620 --> 00:01:09,899
I know, I know, just
let me do my job, okay?

6
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:10,900
Mm-hmm.

7
00:01:22,050 --> 00:01:23,050
Faye!

8
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:26,519
Faye!

9
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:28,249
You in there?

10
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:29,083
Hey Faye!

11
00:01:29,084 --> 00:01:30,569
The neighbors are complaining!

12
00:01:30,570 --> 00:01:33,973
You gotta start taking
your trash out more often.

13
00:01:35,730 --> 00:01:37,479
Faye!

14
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:39,759
Faye, I'm starting to get worried.

15
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,329
Nobody's seen you for a couple of days.

16
00:01:42,330 --> 00:01:43,679
Old Mrs. Hamill,

17
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:46,699
she's driving me nuts
wanting you out here.

18
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:47,700
Faye!

19
00:01:48,850 --> 00:01:50,569
I'm going to come in now.

20
00:01:50,570 --> 00:01:51,570
Okay?

21
00:02:01,650 --> 00:02:04,503
This living like an animal
has got to stop, Faye!

22
00:02:11,220 --> 00:02:12,220
Jesus Christ!

23
00:03:00,650 --> 00:03:02,150
She is definitely a fighter.

24
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,490
It's amazing she survived at all.

25
00:03:07,032 --> 00:03:08,799
I don't hold out much
hope for her to come out

26
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,097
of the coma though.

27
00:03:20,745 --> 00:03:22,969
Heartbeat is strong.

28
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:25,869
We'll just keep her on the
iv and keep her comfortable,

29
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:28,099
for however long it takes
nature to take its course.

30
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,400
Of course, doctor.

31
00:03:29,401 --> 00:03:30,401
Thank you.

32
00:04:33,603 --> 00:04:38,436
Not now, Charlie, mamma's
tired, just five more minutes.

33
00:04:39,686 --> 00:04:40,713
Mrs. King?

34
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:50,753
Dr. Armstrong, she spoke.

35
00:04:51,881 --> 00:04:52,714
Who?

36
00:04:52,715 --> 00:04:54,083
Mrs. King, the coma patient.

37
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:02,679
I was just bathing her
and she began to speak.

38
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:03,954
What did she say?

39
00:05:03,955 --> 00:05:04,788
Was she lucid?

40
00:05:04,789 --> 00:05:06,589
No, I don't think so,
because she called me Charlie.

41
00:05:06,590 --> 00:05:08,819
It was more like muttering in her sleep,

42
00:05:08,820 --> 00:05:10,589
but in case she woke up
I thought it was best

43
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:11,590
to have you here.

44
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:13,889
Yeah, it may have been nothing,

45
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:15,529
just a side effect of her condition.

46
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:16,799
But in the event she comes around,

47
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,609
I did want to be present, you're right.

48
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:20,199
Mrs. King, can you hear me?

49
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,713
Hey, what the hell?

50
00:05:23,876 --> 00:05:25,233
Of course I can hear you

51
00:05:26,815 --> 00:05:28,246
Hi,
Mrs. King, my name is-

52
00:05:28,247 --> 00:05:29,632
- who are you people?

53
00:05:29,633 --> 00:05:31,389
Calm down, Mrs. King,
I'm trying to tell you.

54
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:34,389
My name is Dr. Armstrong,
you're in hospice.

55
00:05:34,390 --> 00:05:36,790
And this is your attending
nurse, Linda dermont.

56
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:40,253
What am I doing in hospice?

57
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:44,119
You were in the hospital
for the first few days,

58
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,670
then they transferred you here.

59
00:05:46,810 --> 00:05:47,643
Days?

60
00:05:47,644 --> 00:05:48,964
Yes, you've been here

61
00:05:48,965 --> 00:05:49,917
for the rest of the week.

62
00:05:49,917 --> 00:05:50,750
Oh, god.

63
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:53,333
Who's been taking care of my cat, Charlie?

64
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,099
What?

65
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,309
Say it!

66
00:05:57,310 --> 00:05:59,209
I'm afraid your animal passed ma'am.

67
00:05:59,210 --> 00:06:01,359
It was the smell of the cat
that caused your landlord

68
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,210
to enter your apartment and find you.

69
00:06:04,793 --> 00:06:05,793
Poor Charlie.

70
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,140
What happened to me?

71
00:06:09,141 --> 00:06:10,839
Why am I here?

72
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,349
You suffered a coma.

73
00:06:12,350 --> 00:06:15,379
From a condition called
alcoholic encephalopathy.

74
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:18,049
It's a build up of ammoniac in the blood.

75
00:06:18,050 --> 00:06:22,763
Apparently from prolonged,
excessive use of alcohol.

76
00:06:24,370 --> 00:06:26,729
Prolonged, excessive
use of alcohol, yeah,

77
00:06:26,730 --> 00:06:28,939
that's an understatement, doc.

78
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,113
But you're awake now!

79
00:06:30,114 --> 00:06:31,393
That's a good sign.

80
00:06:31,394 --> 00:06:33,189
It's a step in the right direction.

81
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:35,029
Let's see if we can make
you more comfortable.

82
00:06:35,030 --> 00:06:36,604
Can you try and raise the bed?

83
00:06:36,605 --> 00:06:37,605
Sure.

84
00:06:47,967 --> 00:06:49,243
There you go, that's better.

85
00:06:50,330 --> 00:06:51,479
I'd like to start off by seeing

86
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,619
if we can get a little food into you.

87
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,019
Bring some of your strength back.

88
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:55,199
Whatever you say, doc.

89
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,579
I'll be back to check on you later.

90
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:57,599
Linda will handle everything.

91
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,068
I'll see you when I'm on my rounds.

92
00:06:59,069 --> 00:07:00,069
Okay.

93
00:07:13,325 --> 00:07:16,158
God damn, I could use a cigarette.

94
00:07:40,685 --> 00:07:43,219
They're not being
completely honest with you.

95
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:44,739
You know that, don't you?

96
00:07:44,740 --> 00:07:47,290
What are you, one of the
resident care takers here?

97
00:07:49,464 --> 00:07:50,969
No.

98
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:54,943
I'm only here when someone
is on their way out,

99
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,389
shall we say.

100
00:07:57,390 --> 00:07:59,943
You see, Faye, these are your final hours.

101
00:08:01,135 --> 00:08:05,063
I've heard of budget cutbacks
before, but this is insane.

102
00:08:06,230 --> 00:08:08,773
I can't be going home
already, I just woke up.

103
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:12,509
I believe what my coadjutor

104
00:08:12,510 --> 00:08:15,199
is trying to relay, Mrs. King, is that,

105
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,079
you're not going to recover from this,

106
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:19,529
and unfortunately one of
US will be guiding you

107
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:20,530
to the afterlife.

108
00:08:23,792 --> 00:08:24,929
What is this?

109
00:08:24,930 --> 00:08:26,813
Some kind of corn ball intervention?

110
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,279
An intervention would
do you little good now,

111
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,403
don't you think, Faye?

112
00:08:33,710 --> 00:08:35,863
This is the end of your mortal life.

113
00:08:36,890 --> 00:08:40,963
All that remains is to determine
where your soul is bound.

114
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,523
Get the hell out of my room!

115
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:48,999
Just woke up and already
in a mood, Mrs. King?

116
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,013
I'm sorry, but the doctor insists
you try and eat something.

117
00:08:52,963 --> 00:08:53,796
I wasn't talking to you.

118
00:08:53,797 --> 00:08:57,453
I was talking to that pale bastard.

119
00:08:58,490 --> 00:09:01,299
I don't think I know
who you're talking about.

120
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:02,300
I'm sorry.

121
00:09:02,301 --> 00:09:06,129
I'm not really that hungry but
I could sure use a cigarette.

122
00:09:06,130 --> 00:09:09,169
I'm sorry, Mrs. King, but
there's no smoking at hospice,

123
00:09:09,170 --> 00:09:10,769
not even for the staff.

124
00:09:10,770 --> 00:09:13,449
So, there's no cigarettes
to be found around here.

125
00:09:13,450 --> 00:09:14,849
But please, try and eat something,

126
00:09:14,850 --> 00:09:17,139
it will make the doctor happy.

127
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:20,639
I'm not making any promises,
but I'll give it a shot.

128
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:22,209
I appreciate the effort.

129
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:23,210
Thank you.

130
00:09:28,230 --> 00:09:30,767
So life didn't turn
out the best for you.

131
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,550
Did it, Faye?

132
00:09:47,814 --> 00:09:50,199
I really don't understand the necessity

133
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,829
of these training exercises anyway.

134
00:09:52,830 --> 00:09:56,929
Isn't your primary
concern disaster relief?

135
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:57,763
Oh, sweetie, come on.

136
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:59,559
I told you this a million times before.

137
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,769
We've gotta be prepared for anything,

138
00:10:01,770 --> 00:10:03,763
that includes military actions.

139
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,083
Yeah, I know, but,

140
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:10,559
I just wish you'd be doing
something less dangerous.

141
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:12,699
I hate the guns.

142
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:14,600
Oh, you'd have me retire
if you could right now,

143
00:10:14,601 --> 00:10:15,434
wouldn't you?

144
00:10:15,435 --> 00:10:16,569
Well, yeah, maybe you
thought, should think

145
00:10:16,570 --> 00:10:19,569
about staying home and
just doing the one job.

146
00:10:19,570 --> 00:10:20,799
The bottom line right now, sweetie,

147
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:24,033
is that our son's college
isn't cheap, ya know?

148
00:10:25,608 --> 00:10:26,608
Yeah.

149
00:10:27,626 --> 00:10:28,989
Come here.

150
00:10:28,990 --> 00:10:32,099
Listen, everything is going to be okay.

151
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,053
Enjoy everything and let it happen.

152
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:36,979
Because I'm in the reserves,

153
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:39,469
we're doing a lot better
than other people right now.

154
00:10:39,470 --> 00:10:42,869
You're gonna have me all to
yourself, 24/7 soon enough,

155
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:45,719
and then you're just going to be begging

156
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,423
for a weekend to yourself.

157
00:10:49,205 --> 00:10:50,060
That is never going to happen,

158
00:10:50,061 --> 00:10:51,759
because I'm never going to
get tired of spending time

159
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:52,593
with you.

160
00:10:52,594 --> 00:10:53,729
You sure?

161
00:10:53,730 --> 00:10:56,269
Yeah, so can you just like
call in sick just this weekend?

162
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:58,159
And maybe go next month
when you're doing something

163
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,759
less dangerous, like

164
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,162
soup dishing exercises?

165
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,720
Oh, sweetie.

166
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:06,036
Do you have any idea how many soldiers

167
00:11:06,037 --> 00:11:07,969
are having this same conversation

168
00:11:07,970 --> 00:11:09,749
with their husbands and wives?

169
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:13,529
If that was the case,
there would be no reserves.

170
00:11:13,530 --> 00:11:15,726
I know, and I can't speak for the rest.

171
00:11:15,727 --> 00:11:19,088
I'll just do my best to try
to convince you to stay.

172
00:11:19,089 --> 00:11:20,212
Yeah?

173
00:11:20,213 --> 00:11:21,213
Yeah.

174
00:11:22,013 --> 00:11:23,811
And how's that?

175
00:11:23,812 --> 00:11:25,229
Shut up.

176
00:11:26,237 --> 00:11:27,735
I'm going to be back, I promise.

177
00:11:27,736 --> 00:11:28,613
Okay?

178
00:11:28,613 --> 00:11:29,446
You better.

179
00:11:29,446 --> 00:11:30,446
I love you.

180
00:11:38,370 --> 00:11:41,229
Disturbing and sad
news out of fort Luke.

181
00:11:41,230 --> 00:11:42,860
Though full details are not released yet,

182
00:11:42,861 --> 00:11:45,785
the military has verified
reports from earlier today

183
00:11:45,786 --> 00:11:47,500
that a soldier has been killed during

184
00:11:47,501 --> 00:11:50,220
routine maneuvers on base.

185
00:11:50,221 --> 00:11:51,519
Oh, no!

186
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:52,609
The military maintains

187
00:11:52,610 --> 00:11:56,239
this was an unfortunate accident
and not an act of terror.

188
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:57,739
Full details will be made public,

189
00:11:57,740 --> 00:11:59,604
including the name of the fallen soldier,

190
00:11:59,605 --> 00:12:03,444
once their family has been
notified of the accident.

191
00:12:03,445 --> 00:12:04,566
Our thoughts and our prayers

192
00:12:04,567 --> 00:12:07,643
are with the fallen soldier's family.

193
00:12:17,816 --> 00:12:18,816
No, John no!

194
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,329
Where's my husband, John?

195
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:27,163
Where is he?

196
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:27,996
Mrs. King?

197
00:12:27,996 --> 00:12:28,970
Yes, I'm Mrs. King, goddammit!

198
00:12:28,971 --> 00:12:30,549
Where's John?

199
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,426
I'm sorry, Mrs. King.

200
00:12:31,427 --> 00:12:33,535
There's been an accident.

201
00:12:33,536 --> 00:12:35,914
Oh god, no, John!

202
00:12:35,915 --> 00:12:38,020
Oh god, no, John!

203
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:47,679
I'm afraid this doesn't get any easier.

204
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:48,999
Let's get her inside.

205
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,000
Okay.

206
00:12:54,592 --> 00:12:59,539
I just don't understand
how this could have happened.

207
00:12:59,540 --> 00:13:01,973
John said it was target practice.

208
00:13:03,070 --> 00:13:05,479
If it was just a routine exercise,

209
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,733
how could he get hurt?

210
00:13:10,637 --> 00:13:14,769
Target practice is a
very routine exercise.

211
00:13:14,770 --> 00:13:17,259
But we do use live rounds.

212
00:13:17,260 --> 00:13:19,203
So, we have to be really careful.

213
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:25,123
Another soldier, he was a new recruit.

214
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,320
His gun jammed.

215
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:30,943
So John came over to
help him clear it out.

216
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:35,493
During that process, the gun
malfunctioned and went off.

217
00:13:36,407 --> 00:13:38,659
The bullet ricocheted off
the wall and struck John

218
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:39,660
in the head.

219
00:13:42,770 --> 00:13:44,233
John was killed instantly.

220
00:13:49,843 --> 00:13:52,909
Mrs. King, if there is anything, anything

221
00:13:52,910 --> 00:13:53,939
at all that we can do

222
00:13:53,940 --> 00:13:56,143
to make this difficult time easier,

223
00:13:57,130 --> 00:13:59,853
just let US know, we
would be glad to help.

224
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:03,466
What my lieutenant was trying to say-

225
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:04,467
- my son.

226
00:14:07,283 --> 00:14:10,143
Mrs. King, what do you mean by your son?

227
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:20,150
I'm sorry.

228
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,400
I'm sorry.

229
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:26,453
Excuse me, our son Todd.

230
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:32,533
He comes home from college in a few days.

231
00:14:33,550 --> 00:14:36,393
And this news is going to destroy him.

232
00:14:42,347 --> 00:14:45,499
If there is any way that
the army could be here,

233
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:47,403
to help me break the news to him.

234
00:14:48,830 --> 00:14:49,830
It would,

235
00:14:51,008 --> 00:14:52,839
it would let Todd know that his father's

236
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:55,085
life meant something.

237
00:14:55,086 --> 00:14:56,403
That he was important.

238
00:15:00,580 --> 00:15:02,206
Mrs. King, I understand that

239
00:15:02,207 --> 00:15:04,309
but the military doesn't usually-

240
00:15:04,310 --> 00:15:06,219
- of course, Mrs. King.

241
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:07,839
Whatever it is you need.

242
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,863
Just let me know when and
where and I'll be there.

243
00:15:20,099 --> 00:15:21,099
Faye.

244
00:15:23,914 --> 00:15:25,927
You had no blame in what happened to John.

245
00:15:27,389 --> 00:15:29,806
Of course not, I know that.

246
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:33,073
It was an accident.

247
00:15:35,926 --> 00:15:38,269
You had no way of knowing
that he was going off

248
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,049
to die that weekend.

249
00:15:40,050 --> 00:15:41,050
Did you, Faye?

250
00:15:41,805 --> 00:15:43,503
No, how could I have known?

251
00:15:46,189 --> 00:15:47,749
What do you mean?

252
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:49,733
What do
you think I mean, Faye?

253
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:53,629
There's no way I could have known.

254
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:58,579
And yet, you tried so
hard to keep him from going.

255
00:15:58,580 --> 00:15:59,623
Why did you do that?

256
00:16:01,202 --> 00:16:02,952
Because I, because-

257
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:05,230
- had a feeling?

258
00:16:06,820 --> 00:16:09,249
Maybe an intuition that John shouldn't go

259
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:10,350
to guard that weekend?

260
00:16:11,442 --> 00:16:13,342
That maybe something bad might happen.

261
00:16:14,950 --> 00:16:19,030
Perhaps if you'd only tried

262
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:23,883
just a little bit harder.

263
00:16:37,727 --> 00:16:40,739
What the hell do you want from me?

264
00:16:40,740 --> 00:16:42,959
I'm sorry, if you're up
to trying to eat something,

265
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,239
I can take it away.

266
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,289
I just thought maybe you
wanted a straw or something,

267
00:16:46,290 --> 00:16:47,123
