00:28:27,670 --> 00:28:28,819
Not to US.

538
00:28:28,820 --> 00:28:30,870
Not after everything we've had to endure.

539
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:33,623
It's not their fault.

540
00:28:38,580 --> 00:28:39,580
You know if,

541
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:43,019
if Todd wasn't here,
we would have lost him

542
00:28:43,020 --> 00:28:44,973
to pneumonia weeks ago.

543
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,639
Maybe so, but I'm not sure

544
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:50,723
this is what's best for him anymore.

545
00:28:55,590 --> 00:28:57,619
Dr bullard, how is he?

546
00:28:57,620 --> 00:28:59,299
Can we see him now?

547
00:28:59,300 --> 00:29:01,732
He's weak, but he can
see visitors for a bit.

548
00:29:01,733 --> 00:29:03,239
What about his lungs?

549
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:04,479
How are his lungs?

550
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:06,829
I'm afraid he's still retaining fluids.

551
00:29:06,830 --> 00:29:07,999
We just don't know exactly how

552
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:11,213
to treat these new drug
resistant strains of aids.

553
00:29:14,915 --> 00:29:16,840
When's the last time you got tested, son?

554
00:29:17,943 --> 00:29:19,139
Just last week.

555
00:29:19,140 --> 00:29:20,779
I've been going to an anonymous clinic

556
00:29:20,780 --> 00:29:23,279
every couple of weeks,
just like you suggested.

557
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:24,979
This is crap!

558
00:29:24,980 --> 00:29:25,813
You shouldn't have.

559
00:29:25,814 --> 00:29:27,649
You should be able to
go to your own doctor,

560
00:29:27,650 --> 00:29:29,883
you shouldn't have to hide!

561
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:32,449
I'm sorry!

562
00:29:32,450 --> 00:29:33,729
I hate the military!

563
00:29:33,730 --> 00:29:35,389
I hate it!

564
00:29:35,390 --> 00:29:37,549
I'm sorry, Mrs. King.

565
00:29:37,550 --> 00:29:39,789
I know this is hard,
but we've got to manage

566
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:42,969
the best we can with the
circumstances we've been given.

567
00:29:42,970 --> 00:29:44,909
Maybe some day, things will be different.

568
00:29:44,910 --> 00:29:46,499
I know, I'm sorry.

569
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:48,933
But we've got to survive today.

570
00:29:50,121 --> 00:29:51,413
I know, you're right.

571
00:29:53,170 --> 00:29:54,303
This is about Todd.

572
00:29:55,980 --> 00:29:58,149
Why don't you take a
minute, splash some water

573
00:29:58,150 --> 00:29:59,779
on your face and we'll go see him.

574
00:29:59,780 --> 00:30:01,736
Okay, thank you.

575
00:30:01,737 --> 00:30:03,320
I'll be right back.

576
00:30:15,676 --> 00:30:17,236
Hi honey.

577
00:30:17,237 --> 00:30:18,110
Ma?

578
00:30:18,111 --> 00:30:19,360
Richie is here with me.

579
00:30:21,350 --> 00:30:23,149
Hey buddy.

580
00:30:23,150 --> 00:30:24,759
Dad's grave?

581
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:27,689
We went yesterday and
put fresh flowers on it.

582
00:30:27,690 --> 00:30:30,199
I know how important it is to you.

583
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:32,320
We won't miss a Sunday, I promise.

584
00:30:34,170 --> 00:30:35,497
I'll be home soon.

585
00:30:38,150 --> 00:30:41,818
Makes me feel better, that
you guys will come visit me

586
00:30:41,819 --> 00:30:43,102
when I'm-

587
00:30:44,590 --> 00:30:46,019
- Don't say that.

588
00:30:46,020 --> 00:30:47,909
You have to hang on.

589
00:30:47,910 --> 00:30:50,360
They are going to figure
out a way to treat this.

590
00:30:51,410 --> 00:30:52,899
You'll see.

591
00:30:57,780 --> 00:31:00,093
Todd, you've got to take it easy.

592
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:03,609
You are not getting enough oxygen.

593
00:31:03,610 --> 00:31:04,860
Speak a little at a time.

594
00:31:12,871 --> 00:31:15,279
Richie and I were talking,

595
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:17,709
since your condition is not changing,

596
00:31:17,710 --> 00:31:20,179
we thought maybe we would
get you some in home care

597
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:21,730
and take you back home with US.

598
00:31:24,089 --> 00:31:26,114
- Faye.
- Sound good?

599
00:31:26,115 --> 00:31:26,948
That's not a good idea.

600
00:31:26,949 --> 00:31:28,139
It's critical that we keep him here

601
00:31:28,140 --> 00:31:29,890
until we can control the pneumonia.

602
00:31:30,830 --> 00:31:32,089
I wanna go home.

603
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:33,659
I know you do, baby.

604
00:31:33,660 --> 00:31:35,060
And we want you there too.

605
00:31:36,020 --> 00:31:37,370
We'll figure something out.

606
00:31:40,755 --> 00:31:43,531
Todd, I need you to rest some more.

607
00:31:43,532 --> 00:31:45,179
Can I speak to you in
the hall for a minute?

608
00:31:45,180 --> 00:31:46,749
Sure.

609
00:31:46,750 --> 00:31:48,583
We will be right back.

610
00:31:50,131 --> 00:31:51,548
I'm going home!

611
00:31:55,331 --> 00:31:56,414
Soon, Todd,

612
00:31:57,848 --> 00:31:58,848
soon,

613
00:32:00,727 --> 00:32:01,727
you'll see.

614
00:32:18,010 --> 00:32:20,319
Look, I know you two want to comfort him,

615
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:21,669
but I think it's best
that we keep him here,

616
00:32:21,670 --> 00:32:24,073
so he can get the best possible care.

617
00:32:25,008 --> 00:32:27,189
Yeah, but we could
get him a nurse at home.

618
00:32:27,190 --> 00:32:28,849
Faye.

619
00:32:28,850 --> 00:32:30,259
His condition is so frail right now,

620
00:32:30,260 --> 00:32:31,810
he would not survive that trip.

621
00:32:33,091 --> 00:32:35,169
Look, everybody knows he's
gonna die and there's nothing

622
00:32:35,170 --> 00:32:36,908
anybody can do about it.

623
00:32:36,909 --> 00:32:37,742
Richard!

624
00:32:37,743 --> 00:32:40,199
But at least he can
do it at home with US,

625
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,569
the people who love him.

626
00:32:41,570 --> 00:32:44,419
Not here surrounded by
a bunch of strangers.

627
00:32:44,420 --> 00:32:46,420
We're doing everything we can for him,

628
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:50,149
but his condition is
gradually getting worse.

629
00:32:50,150 --> 00:32:52,699
If we can get the fluid
off his lungs, I'd be happy

630
00:32:52,700 --> 00:32:54,309
to send him home with you.

631
00:32:54,310 --> 00:32:56,809
But I strongly advise against it.

632
00:32:56,810 --> 00:32:58,739
I wasn't exaggerating when I said

633
00:32:58,740 --> 00:33:00,340
he would not make the trip home.

634
00:33:01,740 --> 00:33:04,710
Dr. Bullard, he is flat-lining again.

635
00:33:04,711 --> 00:33:06,083
Go to the waiting room.

636
00:33:06,084 --> 00:33:07,194
I can't have you in there when
we're trying to do our jobs.

637
00:33:07,195 --> 00:33:08,699
Yeah, but he could
die and we should be in there.

638
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:10,283
Mrs. King, for Todd's sake!

639
00:33:11,704 --> 00:33:14,323
But he's coming home with US!

640
00:33:14,324 --> 00:33:15,324
Oh god!

641
00:33:31,950 --> 00:33:32,993
Dr. Bullard?

642
00:33:36,218 --> 00:33:37,911
I'm sorry, Faye.

643
00:33:37,912 --> 00:33:40,397
There was nothing we could do.

644
00:33:40,398 --> 00:33:41,398
No.

645
00:33:43,237 --> 00:33:44,237
No.

646
00:33:44,997 --> 00:33:46,537
Toddie!

647
00:33:46,538 --> 00:33:49,162
Oh, no!

648
00:34:04,522 --> 00:34:07,099
I just don't know what I
have to live for anymore.

649
00:34:07,100 --> 00:34:08,833
What is left for me here?

650
00:34:09,710 --> 00:34:10,833
I'm still here.

651
00:34:12,620 --> 00:34:13,590
I know you are.

652
00:34:13,591 --> 00:34:15,023
I'm sorry, Richard.

653
00:34:16,200 --> 00:34:18,109
You just have no idea what
it's like for me to have

654
00:34:18,110 --> 00:34:21,553
to get up every single day
and deal with that pain.

655
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,489
I just want it to be over.

656
00:34:24,490 --> 00:34:25,933
Don't I know, ma?

657
00:34:27,971 --> 00:34:28,971
You know,

658
00:34:29,790 --> 00:34:32,349
there's something I need to tell you.

659
00:34:32,350 --> 00:34:35,466
Something that I've, I've
hung on to, because it was,

660
00:34:35,467 --> 00:34:38,649
well, it was just too
much for me to share.

661
00:34:38,650 --> 00:34:41,053
But, I really think it's you knew.

662
00:34:42,620 --> 00:34:44,393
Shortly after we lost, Todd,

663
00:34:46,750 --> 00:34:47,873
I was gonna end it.

664
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:51,899
I had a gun in my mouth and everything.

665
00:34:51,900 --> 00:34:53,350
I was gonna pull the trigger.

666
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:56,729
And then you called, and
then you made me promise

667
00:34:56,730 --> 00:34:58,439
to come over the next day.

668
00:35:28,576 --> 00:35:29,849
Hello?

669
00:35:29,850 --> 00:35:31,532
Hi ya, Richie, honey.

670
00:35:31,533 --> 00:35:33,033
How ya holding up?

671
00:35:35,046 --> 00:35:37,743
Not so good, ma.

672
00:35:37,744 --> 00:35:39,322
How are you doing?

673
00:35:39,323 --> 00:35:40,365
About the same.

674
00:35:40,366 --> 00:35:42,555
I don't know what I would've done

675
00:35:42,556 --> 00:35:45,823
or how I would've gotten
through the day without you.

676
00:35:50,046 --> 00:35:51,496
You know he loved you, right?

677
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:54,200
Yeah, I know.

678
00:35:56,061 --> 00:35:59,289
It was as mutual as it gets.

679
00:35:59,290 --> 00:36:01,839
So I gotta take care
of you now, all right?

680
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:03,840
'Cause that's what Todd would've wanted.

681
00:36:05,570 --> 00:36:07,943
Just like you did for
US, when we lost John.

682
00:36:10,022 --> 00:36:10,855
I don't know, ma.

683
00:36:10,856 --> 00:36:12,447
I just,

684
00:36:12,448 --> 00:36:14,148
I don't think I can keep going on.

685
00:36:15,344 --> 00:36:16,609
Sure you can.

686
00:36:16,610 --> 00:36:18,383
Listen to me, you have to!

687
00:36:19,546 --> 00:36:23,023
You're all I've got left
in this world now, Richie.

688
00:36:24,420 --> 00:36:25,963
Without you by my side,

689
00:36:28,130 --> 00:36:29,903
I haven't got a chance.

690
00:36:31,470 --> 00:36:32,470
Can you, uh,

691
00:36:34,450 --> 00:36:37,569
can you come by the
house tomorrow, please?

692
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:39,470
I've got something I want to show you.

693
00:36:41,275 --> 00:36:43,112
I just, I don't know if I can.

694
00:36:43,113 --> 00:36:44,639
Sure you can.

695
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,263
Listen to me, you have to!

696
00:36:47,230 --> 00:36:49,803
You're all I've got left
in this world now, Richie.

697
00:36:51,248 --> 00:36:52,999
Well, I'll see what I can do.

698
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,169
I gotta go.

699
00:36:54,170 --> 00:36:55,003
No, Richie.

700
00:36:55,004 --> 00:36:56,949
You gotta promise me first!

701
00:36:56,950 --> 00:36:59,500
Promise me you'll be here
tomorrow, it's important.

702
00:37:02,667 --> 00:37:04,089
Okay, okay.

703
00:37:04,090 --> 00:37:04,923
Okay fine.

704
00:37:04,923 --> 00:37:05,756
I promise.

705
00:37:05,756 --> 00:37:06,756
Thank you.

706
00:37:08,250 --> 00:37:10,799
I'll see you in the morning, Richie.

707
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,912
Try and get some sleep.

708
00:37:12,913 --> 00:37:15,383
And remember, I love you.

709
00:37:16,865 --> 00:37:19,318
I love you, ma.

710
00:37:19,319 --> 00:37:20,213
Goodnight.

711
00:37:20,214 --> 00:37:21,482
I'll see you tomorrow.

712
00:37:21,483 --> 00:37:23,045
Bye.

713
00:37:30,557 --> 00:37:32,163
If you hadn't done that, I-

714
00:37:35,795 --> 00:37:37,583
- you never told me this before.

715
00:37:38,710 --> 00:37:40,749
There was never a point.

716
00:37:40,750 --> 00:37:42,819
And what's the point now?

717
00:37:42,820 --> 00:37:45,419
To let you see how important you are.

718
00:37:45,420 --> 00:37:47,159
If you hadn't stopped me that night,

719
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,893
I wouldn't be here now.

720
00:37:50,810 --> 00:37:53,495
Sounds like some kind of emotional ploy

721
00:37:53,496 --> 00:37:55,962
to get me to stop drinking, right?

722
00:37:55,963 --> 00:37:58,269
Well, uh, let's just call it

723
00:37:58,270 --> 00:37:59,963
motivation to get better.

724
00:38:02,650 --> 00:38:04,119
Have you had a nice visit?

725
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:06,539
Uh-oh, warden is here to kick me out.

726
00:38:06,540 --> 00:38:08,599
Now, don't be like that, Mr. Paul.

727
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:11,629
I'm just doing what's best
for Mrs. King's health.

728
00:38:11,630 --> 00:38:14,579
And doctor's orders are 30 minutes Max.

729
00:38:14,580 --> 00:38:16,249
She needs her rest if she's gonna get out

730
00:38:16,250 --> 00:38:17,563
of here any time soon.

731
00:38:19,330 --> 00:38:21,080
I know, Linda, I was just joking.

732
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:24,379
I will see you tomorrow.

733
00:38:24,380 --> 00:38:25,639
You keep getting better, okay?

734
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:26,740
And I'll see you then.

735
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,029
Thanks for taking care of her.

736
00:38:29,030 --> 00:38:31,339
She's a lot more special
than you can imagine.

737
00:38:31,340 --> 00:38:33,059
I can imagine.

738
00:38:33,060 --> 00:38:35,629
You have a good night, Mr. Paul,
and we'll see you tomorrow.

739
00:38:35,630 --> 00:38:36,620
You too, Linda.

740
00:38:36,620 --> 00:38:37,453
Goodnight, ma.

741
00:38:37,454 --> 00:38:38,699
Night, Richie.

742
00:38:38,700 --> 00:38:39,753
I'll see you tomorrow.

743
00:38:42,020 --> 00:38:44,753
Now, how are you feeling
after a nap and a visit?

744
00:38:44,754 --> 00:38:47,759
Oh, god, overwhelmed!

745
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:51,289
Okay, not the answer I was expecting.

746
00:38:51,290 --> 00:38:53,549
I was hoping for hungry.

747
00:38:53,550 --> 00:38:55,629
Well, I could use a cig-

748
00:38:55,630 --> 00:38:56,623
- Cigarette?

749
00:38:56,623 --> 00:38:57,456
Yeah!

750
00:38:57,457 --> 00:39:00,749
Yes, Mrs. King, I know,
but it ain't gonna happen.

751
00:39:00,750 --> 00:39:02,519
How about some warm broth?

752
00:39:02,520 --> 00:39:05,217
It will help you get your strength back.

753
00:39:05,218 --> 00:39:07,609
Well, it's not a smoke,
but I'll give it a try.

754
00:39:07,610 --> 00:39:10,379
Fantastic, I'll be
back in a few minutes.

755
00:39:10,380 --> 00:39:11,380
Thank you.

756
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:21,410
It was nice of Richard

757
00:39:21,411 --> 00:39:22,529
to come all the way back from Europe

758
00:39:22,530 --> 00:39:24,283
to check in on you.

759
00:39:24,284 --> 00:39:25,117
Oh, god.

760
00:39:25,117 --> 00:39:25,950
You again.

761
00:39:25,951 --> 00:39:27,320
So, where's your fancy friend?

762
00:39:28,290 --> 00:39:29,490
He's never far behind.

763
00:39:30,750 --> 00:39:32,539
I'm here, Faye.

764
00:39:32,540 --> 00:39:33,373
Oh, god.

765
00:39:33,374 --> 00:39:35,972
I was just being sarcastic.

766
00:39:35,973 --> 00:39:37,599
I wasn't really asking for you.

767
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:39,619
Yeah, I realize that.

768
00:39:39,620 --> 00:39:43,599
But you need to understand,
our business here isn't done.

769
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:46,333
How does what the soldier
told you make you feel?

770
00:39:47,240 --> 00:39:52,240
Where do you jerks get off
questioning me about my family?

771
00:39:52,420 --> 00:39:54,259
Richie is a good kid.

772
00:39:54,260 --> 00:39:55,849
And Todd?

773
00:39:55,850 --> 00:39:57,223
Was he a good kid as well?

774
00:39:58,350 --> 00:40:02,973
And were you okay with their relationship?

775
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:11,169
So tell me more about
the movie, was it any good?

776
00:40:11,170 --> 00:40:14,789
Well, good is a relative term, I guess.

777
00:40:14,790 --> 00:40:17,089
Yeah, Todd hated it.

778
00:40:17,090 --> 00:40:18,929
I think hated is a bit harsh.

779
00:40:18,930 --> 00:40:19,763
I just like a little bit

780
00:40:19,764 --> 00:40:22,559
of dialog between explosions, is all.

781
00:40:22,560 --> 00:40:24,459
Okay, if you say so.

782
00:40:24,460 --> 00:40:27,359
Wow, since Todd and I have
pretty much the same taste,

783
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:29,299
it's probably not a
movie I want to go see.

784
00:40:29,300 --> 00:40:31,289
That would be putting it mildly.

785
00:40:31,290 --> 00:40:33,939
Well, if you don't mind, I'd
like to change the subject.

786
00:40:33,940 --> 00:40:36,140
There's something I
wanted to ask you about.

787
00:40:37,870 --> 00:40:39,029
Yeah, sure, mom.

788
00:40:39,030 --> 00:40:40,109
What's that?

789
00:40:40,110 --> 00:40:43,529
Well, you're graduating
in a couple months.

790
00:40:43,530 --> 00:40:44,829
Have you given any
thought to where you want

791
00:40:44,830 --> 00:40:46,019
to live when you get back?

792
00:40:46,020 --> 00:40:46,990
I hadn't really thought about it.

793
00:40:46,991 --> 00:40:49,659
I was just concentrating on graduating.

794
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:51,626
And then, I thought I'd come
back home and get settled in

795
00:40:51,627 --> 00:40:53,449
and just go from there.

796
00:40:53,450 --> 00:40:57,473
Well, you know I'd
love to have you here,

797
00:40:58,890 --> 00:41:00,729
but maybe it's time the two of you thought

798
00:41:00,730 --> 00:41:02,311
about moving in together.

799
00:41:04,532 --> 00:41:06,531
Mom!

800
00:41:06,532 --> 00:41:07,390
Mom!

801
00:41:07,390 --> 00:41:08,223
Well, come on.

802
00:41:08,224 --> 00:41:10,159
It's obvious how you two
feel about each other.

803
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:11,748
You know what, maybe I should just go.

804
00:41:11,749 --> 00:41:12,582
